post_text:
Congratulations to MVRHS Senior Jaiden Edelman, one of only three students in Massachusetts given the US Presidential Scholar Award!

Jaiden is 1 of over 5,600 candidates across each who were invited into the program based on his SAT score. He was then named one of 621 semi-finalists based on a number of criteria, including essays, self-assessments, school recommendations and academic performance in high school. He became one of 11 semi-finalists in the state of Massachusetts, and now is 1 of only 3 students in the state to receive the honor of being named a Presidential Scholar. Only 121 students across the country were chosen, and would normally be invited to attend the National Recognition Program held in Washington, DC, which unfortunately cannot occur due to the pandemic.

https://www.bostonglobe.com/2020/05/21/metro/3-mass-high-school-seniors-named-us-presidential-scholars/

post_text: Martha’s Vineyard Regional High School (MVRHS) is proud to announce the 21st annual Science and Engineering Fair to be held on February 8th in the MVRHS cafeteria. More than 30 students will be presenting their investigative and engineering projects on February 8th from 10:00 AM to 12:00. Additionally, students from the school’s Navigator Program will be hosting engineering challenges throughout the public viewing period. The Navigator students will also be selling coffee and tea to raise funds for the Island Autism Group. The event will culminate with the presentation of the fair’s awards at 12:00 PM.

post_text: MVRHS Student Registration is Open on FamilyID, www.familyid.com! All new students and returning students must create and/or update their registration by August 29th! Our MVRHS Fall Sports FamilyID registration will open on July 16th! All Fall Sport Athletes must have both registrations ~ Demographic & Medical and Athletic ~ completed in order to participate! Questions? Check out our website, www.mvrhs.org or please email Jessica Estrella, jestrella@mvyps.org
